This file describes building and using a test application called PasswordServer. 

            How to build
1. To build all parts of this test we need to type:
$./configure ; make
2. Server application will be located in Server directory, Client - in Client directory.
3. To discover database libraries which are used in the test we need to set following environment variables: 
   export PATH=$PATH:~/PasswordServer/Database
   export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=~/PasswordServer/Database
   These variables could be set from .profile file (for system) or from .bashrc file (for user).
   
           How to use
1. Run Server application. You can see a port number from console where is the Server has been started from.
2. Run Client application. You can use "Add", "Update" or "Delete" operations to manipulate users accounts.
            